The paper deals with the architecture of deep convolutional networks and proposes a new approach to reduce the number of parameters without losing performance or to improve performance with the same level of parameters. This is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses regularization techniques, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on image classification tasks, which falls under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
